reviews.review_text: please post 3 2 87 Please post night before love your recordings. And was my fav morning dew from 87.  not that it's about me but it is

- One of my favorite shows. I wouldn't see them for the first time for another three months or so, and this is one of many early '87 shows I'm bummed I missed. See the Dirty Dozen's show from this date (also on the archive) and you'll have the whole show. The encore, with Jerry completely forgetting the lyrics to Brokedown and the crowd singing it for him, is one of the warmest moments in Dead history. He's playing spectacularly through the whole show, as is everybody. Coma? What coma? Fuck the coma, let's play! Mighty Quinn opener signals the upcoming Dylan/Dead summer tour.
